content:
Reconnect your social account for Social Customer Service.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Social Customer Service is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Service Setup is available in Lightning Experience.
Social Customer Service is available in all editions with the Service Cloud.


USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To administer Social Customer Service:	
Manage Users

AND

Customize Application


To create case feed items:	Feed Tracking for All Related Objects on the Case object
To send and receive social media posts or messages:	

Case Feed enabled

AND

Access to a social account

Modify All on social objects


IMPORTANT Effective May 3, 2022, the Social Customer Service Starter Pack is no longer available to customers who haven't previously enabled this feature. Customers who have previously used and configured the SCS Starter Pack can continue to use it. Customers who didn't enable the Starter Pack before this date can only use Social Customer Service if they have a Social Studio account to login to SCS.

Your social account can be disconnected from Social Customer Service if your social media network providerâ€™s connect, or token, has expired.

NOTE

Social Customer Service can experience authentication errors, especially if Network Access is enabled and you are using Social Customer Service with a Connected App. To avoid authentication errors, add your Social Customer Service IP address to Network Access rules in Setup.

From Setup, enter Social Media in the Quick Find box, then select Settings.
On the Social Accounts tab, click Reauthorize in the Action column.
The social network opens and asks you to authenticate the account. Once your account is reauthenticated, you are returned to the Social Accounts tab.
title: Reconnecting a Social Account in Salesforce
